## Creating new entry in Magic Docs app

You are expert in creating interactive learning materials about web technologies, using [tech-stack.mdc](mdc:.cursor/rules/tech-stack.mdc)

Your goal is to create end-to-end solution for <TECHNOLOGY> mentioned by the user.

Execute the following:

1) Make sure that subdirectory `src/catalog` exists
2) Create subdirectory `src/catalog/<TECHNOLOGY>` (kebab-case)
3) In `src/catalog/<TECHNOLOGY>/knowledge.md` create comprehensive yet approachable documentation explaining key aspects of <TECHNOLOGY>
3.1) Focus on three sub-chapters - Why, What, How
4) In `src/catalog/<TECHNOLOGY>/chart-1.md` create mermaid flowchart diagram illustrating key blocks and modules of issues that TECHNOLOGY wants to solve (Why).
5) In `src/catalog/<TECHNOLOGY>/chart-2.md` create mermaid flowchart diagram illustrating key blocks and modules of technology from user perspective (What).
6) In `src/catalog/<TECHNOLOGY>/chart-3.md` create mermaid state diagram illustrating key actions and steps to take to achieve first success with this technology (How).

7) In `src/catalog/<TECHNOLOGY>/{Technology}Diagram{Why|How|What}.tsx` create Three.js interactive 3d diagrams matching exactly what you've build in given chart 1-3, but this time in Three.js and React.

Always use [GithubActionsDiagram.tsx](mdc:src/catalog/github-actions/GithubActionsDiagram.tsx) as a reference (including base diagram [BaseThreeJSDiagram.tsx](mdc:src/shared/components/BaseThreeJSDiagram.tsx))

8) In `src/catalog/<TECHNOLOGY>/{Technology}Page.tsx` create a new React page component that integrates all three diagrams - Why, What and How. Use `knowledge.md` to create interactive Wikipedia-like page incorporating Diagrams and descriptions of each section, with examples in code snippets.


When developing code, always follow [threejs.mdc](mdc:.cursor/rules/threejs.mdc) and [react-development.mdc](mdc:.cursor/rules/react-development.mdc)

Integrate new page with [App.tsx](mdc:src/App.tsx) and embed it as new route.

Make sure there's a new tile added on [HomePage.tsx](mdc:src/pages/HomePage.tsx)